            "contentEn": "# Setting Up Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Welcome!** Before we start coding, we need to set up your computer. Think of this like buying your ingredients before cooking a meal.\r\n\r\nDon't worry if you've never done this before. Just follow the steps one by one.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 1. Get a Web Browser\r\n\r\nYou probably already have this! We recommend **Google Chrome** because it has excellent tools for developers.\r\n\r\n- **Download:** [google.com/chrome](https://google.com/chrome)\r\n- **Install:** Run the file you downloaded and follow the instructions.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 2. Get a Text Editor (VS Code)\r\n\r\nThis is where you will write your code. It's like Microsoft Word, but for programming.\r\n\r\n- **Download:** [code.visualstudio.com](https://code.visualstudio.com/)\r\n- **Install:**\r\n  1. Download the version for your computer (Windows or Mac).\r\n  2. Run the installer.\r\n  3. Click \"Next\" through the options. Default settings are fine!\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 3. Install Node.js\r\n\r\nThis is a tool that lets your computer run JavaScript outside of the browser. It's essential for modern web development.\r\n\r\n- **Download:** [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org/)\r\n- **Important:** Choose the **LTS (Long Term Support)** version. It's the most stable.\r\n- **Install:** Run the installer and click \"Next\" until it's done.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 4. Setup VS Code Extensions\r\n\r\nExtensions make VS Code more powerful.\r\n\r\n1. Open **VS Code**.\r\n2. Click the **Extensions** icon on the left sidebar (it looks like four squares).\r\n3. Search for and install these:\r\n   - **Prettier - Code formatter** (Makes your code look neat)\r\n   - **ES7+ React/Redux/React-Native snippets** (Shortcuts for React)\r\n   - **Tailwind CSS IntelliSense** (Helps with styling later)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 5. Create Your Project Folder\r\n\r\nWe need a place to keep all your work.\r\n\r\n1. Go to your **Desktop** (minimize all windows).\r\n2. Right-click on an empty space -> **New** -> **Folder**.\r\n3. Name it `coding-course`.\r\n4. Open **VS Code**.\r\n5. Go to **File** -> **Open Folder**.\r\n6. Select your new `coding-course` folder.\r\n\r\n**You are now ready to start!** ðŸŽ‰\r\n",
